casebody.data:
Alexander, Appellant, v. BancOhio National Bank, Appellee.

[Cite as Alexander v. BancOhio Natl. Bank (1992), 62 Ohio St.3d 409.]

(No. 91-588 Submitted September 17, 1991 Decided January 29, 1992.) James I. Alexander, pro se. McFadden & Winner and Joseph C. Winner, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The court of appeals did not have jurisdiction. Section 3, Article IV, Ohio Constitution. Consequently, we affirm the judgment of the court of appeals.

Judgment affirmed.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
